    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="1002"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1002">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/2170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-09T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 9, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 9—2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>372. Dr. Leighton Stuart<note n="32" xml:id="d1002fn32">American president of
                        Yenching University, Peiping.</note> who is on friendly terms with General
                    Tada, Commander of the Japanese North China army, was informed <pb facs="0909"
                        n="901" xml:id="pg_901"/> by the General this afternoon during a
                    conversation that he had issued telegraphic instructions yesterday to all
                    military garrisons under his command to give full protection to Americans at
                    this time when tension was increasing.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Tientsin, Shanghai, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
